00:01:13,325 --> 00:01:16,575
Some years ago two gentlemen
went back to Amsterdam...

24
00:01:16,787 --> 00:01:19,360
...saying that Allhevinghay
was just like home.

25
00:01:19,665 --> 00:01:21,325
There was so much water...

26
00:01:21,750 --> 00:01:24,206
...so many ornamental ponds,
so many canals...

27
00:01:24,419 --> 00:01:26,246
...so many sinks and basins.

28
00:01:26,922 --> 00:01:28,416
There was even a wind pump.

29
00:01:29,216 --> 00:01:31,256
What they had not realised was...

30
00:01:31,719 --> 00:01:34,636
...my father had made
his land into a pattern...

31
00:01:34,847 --> 00:01:36,008
...of reservoirs...

32
00:01:36,222 --> 00:01:39,093
...because he was terrified of fire.

33
00:01:39,434 --> 00:01:41,805
There was even a room
under the front stairs...

34
00:01:42,144 --> 00:01:44,433
...that housed two hundred buckets...

35
00:01:44,813 --> 00:01:46,770
...all of them filled with water.

36
00:01:47,358 --> 00:01:50,358
I know because
whenever I was taken short...

37
00:01:50,694 --> 00:01:53,446
...my brothers and I used
to rush in there and use them.

38
00:01:56,784 --> 00:01:59,904
Those buckets were
filled before my mother died.

39
00:02:00,287 --> 00:02:02,363
I expect them to be still there...

40
00:02:02,748 --> 00:02:06,413
...with the same water of thirty years
ago I shouldn't wonder...

41
00:02:07,044 --> 00:02:09,416
...mixed with a
little of myself, of course.

42
00:02:10,298 --> 00:02:12,006
I used to pee like a horse.

43
00:02:12,967 --> 00:02:14,130
I still do.

44
